gp
Class Node

java.lang.Object
  gp.Node

public class Node
extends java.lang.Object

A class the represents a binary tree node. A leaf node has no children. The depth of a node n is the length of the path from the root to the node. The set of all nodes at a given depth is sometimes called a level of the tree. The root node is at depth zero. Siblings are nodes that share the same parent node. If a path exists from node p to node q, where node p is closer to the root node than q, then p is an ancestor of q and q is a descendant of p. The size of a node is the number of descendants it has including itself. In-degree of a node is the number of edges arriving at that node. Out-degree of a node is the number of edges leaving that node.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Trevor Greene
